The paper discusses the design, implementation, and testing of novel abstract solutions for cautious reasoning tasks in ASP, which involves formal analysis of algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with logic and reasoning, which are key topics in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also mentions Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a declarative programming paradigm, and Constraint ASP, which involves solving constraint satisfaction problems, indicating that the paper may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the new solutions in an ASP solver, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
